case.sLatestTextSummary: Also related to 1 and 2, some of the knob ranges seem a bit skewed. For example, it's hard to get the envelope speed just right at the lower end because the speed ramps up too quickly, Even when holding ctrl to "fine tune" it's really hard to get ...

event.evtDescription: Assigned to Scott Metoyer by Scott Metoyer

event.s: Also related to 1 and 2, some of the knob ranges seem a bit skewed. For example, it's hard to get the envelope speed just right at the lower end because the speed ramps up too quickly, Even when holding ctrl to "fine tune" it's really hard to get right and combined with no visual readout this makes it quite frustrating. I'm guessing the knobs value is rising in a linear fashion, perhaps some other curve that allowed more range in the lower frequencies would be better? The pitch knob seems to suffer from the same problem, too much of the range is in a small area at the start of the knobs rotation.

case.sTitle: Ensure oscillators reset with each hit
case.sLatestTextSummary: Are the Oscillators free running? When I look at the output on a scope the phase seems to be moving on each drum hit, which makes me think they are. Normally on percussion modules the oscillator in restarted on each hit so the waveform is identical ...

event.evtDescription: Assigned to Scott Metoyer by Scott Metoyer

event.s: Are the Oscillators free running? When I look at the output on a scope the phase seems to be moving on each drum hit, which makes me think they are. Normally on percussion modules the oscillator in restarted on each hit so the waveform is identical each time, which is the preferred behaviour for percussion. If a bass drum keeps shifting phase it can cause the drums and any accompanying bass to sound different on each hit as the frequencies reinforce or mask each other which is a nightmare to mix!
event.sHtml: Are the Oscillators free running? When I look at the output on a scope the phase seems to be moving on each drum hit, which makes me think they are. Normally on percussion modules the oscillator in restarted on each hit so the waveform is identical each time, which is the preferred behaviour for percussion. If a bass drum keeps shifting phase it can cause the drums and any accompanying bass to sound different on each hit as the frequencies reinforce or mask each other which is a nightmare to mix!
